# School of Business, Publishing & Institutional Strategy

## Purpose
Trains students to build and operate mission-aligned organizations with competencies in publishing operations, digital distribution, and institutional strategy.

## Scope
- business fundamentals, operations, publishing workflow, platform distribution strategy
- Credentials: certificates through MBA-style professional tracks
- Delivery: online/hybrid

## Distinctives
- Real-world operational labs (catalogs, workflows, metadata, discovery)
- Capstone: launch-ready business/publishing plan with metrics